<p>View all types of data that can be compromised in breaches.</p>

<% if defined?(@error) %>
  <div class="error">
    <strong>Error:</strong> <%= @error %>
  </div>
<% end %>

<% if defined?(@success) && @success %>
  <div class="result success">
    <h3>All Data Classes (<%= @result.length %>)</h3>

    <div style="margin-top: 20px;">
      <% @result.sort.each do |data_class| %>
        <span class="badge badge-info"><%= data_class %></span>
      <% end %>
    </div>

    <h4 style="margin-top: 30px;">Raw JSON Response:</h4>
    <pre><%= JSON.pretty_generate(@result) %></pre>
  </div>
<% end %>

<div class="info" style="margin-top: 30px;">
  <h3>About Data Classes</h3>
  <p>Data classes represent the types of information that can be exposed in a data breach. When you look up a breached account, you'll see which of these data types were compromised.</p>
</div>
